In [ ]:
directory_path = os.path.join(".", "drive/MyDrive/balanced")                                #       dataset
filenames_in_directory = glob.glob(os.path.join(directory_path, "*"))                       #         dataset

num_of_images=len(filenames_in_directory)                                                   #         dataset

images = np.zeros((num_of_images, size, size, 3))                                           #       dataset
labels = list()                                                                             #       
for id_filename, filename in enumerate(filenames_in_directory):
    label=filename.split(os.sep)[-1].split("_")[0]                                          #        label
    pill_img=keras.preprocessing.image.load_img(path=filename,                              #      pill_img
                                                color_mode="rgb",                           #   preprocessing  
                                                target_size=(size, size))
    images[id_filename,:,:,:]=keras.preprocessing.image.img_to_array(pill_img)              #      images
    labels.append(label)
print(f"The number of images is equal to {images.shape[0]}")
print(f"The shape of the array is: {images.shape}")
print(f"The data type of the array is: {images.dtype}")     

The number of images is equal to 2552
The shape of the array is: (2552, 128, 128, 3)
The data type of the array is: float64

In [ ]:
kernel_size=(3,3)                                                                                   #      CNN
pooling_size=(2,2)
cnn_model = keras.models.Sequential([keras.layers.RandomTranslation(height_factor=(-0.2, 0.2),      #    CNN 
                                                                    width_factor=(-0.2, 0.2),       #     layers   keras
                                                                    fill_mode="nearest",            # Augmentation  
                                                                    interpolation="bilinear"),
                                     keras.layers.RandomFlip(mode="horizontal"),
                                     keras.layers.RandomRotation(factor=(-0.2, 0.2),
                                                                 fill_mode="nearest",
                                                                 interpolation="bilinear"),
                                     keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32,                                
                                                         kernel_size=kernel_size,
                                                         activation="relu",
                                                         input_shape=(size,size,3)),
                                     keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=pooling_size),
                                     keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=64,
                                                        kernel_size=kernel_size,
                                                        activation="relu"),
                                     keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=pooling_size),
                                     keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=64,
                                                        kernel_size=kernel_size,
                                                        activation="relu"),
                                     keras.layers.Flatten(),
                                     keras.layers.Dropout(rate=0.3),
                                     keras.layers.Dense(units=64, 
                                                        activation="relu"
                                                       ),
                                     keras.layers.Dense(units=11,
                                                        activation="softmax" 
                                                       )
                                    ]
                                   )

(loss function) ("categorical_crossentropy"), "optimizer" "adam" ("accuracy"). .

#   classification report   dictionary

In [ ]:
precision = [report_dict[label]['precision'] for label in class_names]                      #      precision, recall  f1-score
recall = [report_dict[label]['recall'] for label in class_names]                            #      
f1_score = [report_dict[label]['f1-score'] for label in class_names]     

x = range(len(class_names))                                                                 #    x  
width = 0.3                                                                                 #       

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,7))
ax.bar(x, precision, width, label='Precision', color="purple", alpha=0.4)
ax.bar([i + width for i in x], recall, width, label='Recall', color="green", alpha=0.6)

ax.set_xticks([i + width for i in x])
ax.set_xticklabels(class_names)

ax.set_xlabel('Class')
ax.set_ylabel('Score')
ax.set_title('Classification Report')
ax.legend()

for i in x:
    ax.text(i, precision[i], str(round(precision[i], 2)), ha='center', va='bottom')
    ax.text(i + width, recall[i], str(round(recall[i], 2)), ha='center', va='bottom')

plt.show()
In [ ]:
# Obtain the weighted and macro averages from the classification report dictionary
weighted_avg = report_dict['weighted avg']
macro_avg = report_dict['macro avg']

# Extract precision, recall, and F1-score for weighted and macro averages
precision = weighted_avg['precision']
recall = weighted_avg['recall']
f1_score = weighted_avg['f1-score']
# Define the values
metrics = ['Accuracy', 'Precision', 'Recall']
values = [f1_score, precision, recall]

# Plot the bar chart
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
bars = ax.bar(metrics, values, alpha= 0.6)

# Add value labels to each bar
for bar in bars:
    yval = bar.get_height()
    ax.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, yval, round(yval, 2), ha='center', va='bottom')

# Customize the colors of the bars
colors = ['purple', 'green', 'teal']
for bar, color in zip(bars, colors):
    bar.set_color(color)
    

# Set the plot title and labels
plt.title('Average Classification Metrics')
plt.ylabel('Metric Value')

# Display the plot
plt.show()

wrong_predictions = []                                                           #       
cor_preds=[]                                                                     #    labels   
wrong_images=[]                                                                  #           
for i in range(len(test_pred)):
  if test_pred[i] != test_labels[i]:
    wrong_predictions.append(test_pred[i])
    wrong_images.append(test_images[i])
    cor_preds.append(test_labels[i])
